definitions.definition: Used to indicate that the following event, period, or change in state occurred in the past, after a time of waiting, enduring, or anticipation
To move from further away to nearer to.
definitions.example: She’ll be coming ’round the mountain when she comes [...]

definitions.definition: To arrive.
To appear, to manifest itself.
definitions.example: The pain in his leg comes and goes.

definitions.definition: (with an infinitive) To begin to have an opinion or feeling.
definitions.example: She came to think of that country as her home.

definitions.definition: (with an infinitive) To do something by chance, without intending to do it.
definitions.example: Could you tell me how the document came to be discovered?

definitions.definition: To take a position relative to something else in a sequence.
definitions.example: Which letter comes before Y?   Winter comes after autumn.

definitions.definition: To achieve orgasm; to cum; to ejaculate.
definitions.example: He came after a few minutes.

definitions.definition: (with close) To approach a state of being or accomplishment.
definitions.example: One of the screws came loose, and the skateboard fell apart.

definitions.definition: (with to) To take a particular approach or point of view in regard to something.
definitions.example: He came to SF literature a confirmed technophile, and nothing made him happier than to read a manuscript thick with imaginary gizmos and whatzits.

definitions.definition: (fossil word) To become, to turn out to be.
definitions.example: He was a dream come true.

definitions.definition: To be supplied, or made available; to exist.
definitions.example: A new sports car doesn't come cheap.

definitions.definition: To carry through; to succeed in.
definitions.example: You can't come any tricks here.

definitions.definition: Happen.
definitions.example: This kind of accident comes when you are careless.

definitions.definition: (with from or sometimes of) To have as an origin, originate.
(of grain) To germinate.
To pretend to be; to behave in the manner of.
definitions.example: Don't come the innocent victim. We all know who's to blame here.

definitions.definition: To have an orgasm, to feel the sensation of an orgasm.
To ejaculate.
A grooved strip of lead used to hold panes of glass together.
